The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks for time series forecasting, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of LSTM and GRU networks, which are types of neural networks commonly used in time series forecasting (cs.NE). The paper also discusses feature engineering and feature importances, which are common topics in machine learning research (cs.SI). Finally, the paper includes an empirical study using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision research (cs.CV).
